{"Body":"<p>I have some Hebrew (right-to-left) text within an English (left-to-right) text as such:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/03u7Y.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>The Hebrew text (right-to-left) by itself looks like this:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/16Cbv.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>When the <em>paper</em> does not have enough width, the Hebrew text would wrap naturally as such:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/bARgo.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>What's the correct way to write the text when <strong>there is not enough space to finish the right-to-left quote in a single line</strong>?</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Option A:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/ozWJs.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>(note that we have to read the Hebrew text from <em>bottom-up</em> if this is the case)</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Option B:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/lEeQz.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>(aligning the <em>start-of-line</em> of the Hebrew text)</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Option C:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/qIOdT.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>(same as Option B but compacted left)</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Option D:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/9jd5a.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>Option E:</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/vihg9.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<hr>\n", "Id":"3250", "LastEditorUserId":"1756", "FavoriteCount":"2", "AcceptedAnswerId":"3273", "Title":"How are line breaks handled in bidirectional messages containing both English and Hebrew?", "CreationDate":"2013-02-22T19:26:03.667", "OwnerUserId":"998", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<orthography><written-language>", "AnswerCount":"3", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2013-06-03T13:36:43.030", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"4", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"1756", "AccountId":"530146", "Views":"2", "Reputation":"171", "CreationDate":"2013-02-12T13:50:44.847", "DisplayName":"Seth J", "LastAccessDate":"2013-08-27T11:38:46.970"}, "ViewCount":"159", "LastActivityDate":"2013-06-03T13:36:43.030", "Score":"9", "CommentCount":"12", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"22", "Location":"Singapore", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"998", "AccountId":"316665", "Views":"1", "Reputation":"220", "CreationDate":"2012-05-10T21:02:48.840", "DisplayName":"Pacerier", "LastAccessDate":"2014-01-02T04:55:42.250", "AboutMe":"<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elections_in_Singapore#Opposition_views\" rel=\"nofollow\">When the people fear the government, there is tyranny. When governments fear the people, there is liberty.</a></p>\n\n<p>Current status: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conscription_in_Singapore#Enlistment\" rel=\"nofollow\">sold as cheap, forced labour for 11921/16056 hours</a></p>\n", "Age":"23"}}